      "citation_id": "[CITATION_28]",
      "span_text": "The generalizability of these findings to pediatric NAFLD is unclear, however, because the dominant pattern of NASH in children differs from that in adults.  The pediatric pattern is characterized by portal inflammation and/or fibrosis without the ballooning degeneration and perisinusoidal fibrosis typical of adult NASH.  The microstructural differences between pediatric and adult patterns of NASH may affect associations of histologic features and DWI parameters."
